  "title": "Project Manager #77824",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Construction</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Project Manager / Project Engineer</strong></li><li>Working Location: Central (HQ at Kaki Bukit)</li><li>Working Hours: 5.5 days (Mon – Fri, 9.00am – 6.00pm, Sat: 9.00am – 1.00pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + Variable Bonus + Transportation Benefits</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage project lifecycles, ensuring completion within budget, time, and quality standards.</li><li>Adhere to all regulatory and legislative requirements during project phases.</li><li>Plan projects comprehensively and drive them towards successful completion.</li><li>Uphold and enforce standards of safety, sustainability, and environmental, social, and governance (ESG) practices.</li><li>Foster continuous improvement within project operations.</li><li>Effectively communicate and manage relationships with various stakeholders.</li><li>Exhibit resourcefulness, excellent planning, and time management skills.</li><li>Handle multiple projects efficiently under pressure while maintaining a detail-oriented focus.</li><li>Support the performance and well-being of the project team.</li><li>Work across both on-site and office settings.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Degree or higher in Civil Engineering, Project Management, or a related construction discipline.</li><li>3-5 years of experience in project management, preferably with conservation projects or restoration works such as museums, historical buildings, or A&A Works.</li><li>Project Management Professional (PMP) certification is a plus.</li><li>Individuals without experience are encouraged to apply, training is provided.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#77824 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
